<SECOND>AM-Florida Crackdown,0263</SECOND>
<HEAD>Florida Sheriffs Crack Down On Cocaine</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JACKIE HALLIFAX</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Hundreds of local law enforcement officers were buying and selling cocaine Friday in sting operations across the state aimed at slowing down street-level drug traffic. Operation Rock Pile made at least 480 arrests Friday during its first night. `` To our knowledge it's the first time anything like this has been done,'' <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Crolius </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Broward </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Sheriff's spokesman, said in a telephone interview from the <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lauderdale </LOCATION> command center. The <ORGANIZATION> Florida </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sheriffs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> organized the operation. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Doyle </PERSON>, an assistant project director with the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sheriffs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Alexandria </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, said he had never heard of local law enforcement agencies working together in a statewide effort _ although other states have had statewide operations organized from a state level. Fifteen city police departments and at least 61 of <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>'s 66 sheriff's departments are participating, according to <PERSON> Crolius </PERSON>, who estimated that more than 1,000 officers were involved in the project. <LOCATION> Dade </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, which has a countywide police department rather than a sheriff's office, is also participating. The crackdown was scheduled to end midnight Saturday. The operation is targeted equally at buyers and sellers, and includes both `` buy busts,'' which result in the arrests of dealers, and reverse stings, which result in the arrests of users. Search warrants will be served as well. Most arrests will probably be made in urban areas like <LOCATION> Broward </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Dade </LOCATION> counties, the <LOCATION> Orlando </LOCATION> area and <LOCATION> Tampa </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Petersburg </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Crolius </PERSON> said.
</TEXT>
