<ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rhode </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Island </ORGANIZATION> scientists said there apparently had been little permanent environmental damage. About 150 young lobsters, 500 crabs, 15 birds and numerous mussels have died, they said, but most small animals critical to the food chain, such as zooplankton, survived. In <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, the tanker <PERSON> Presidente </PERSON> <PERSON> Rivera </PERSON> leaked up to 1,500 barrels more oil while being cleaned and emptied, but officials said most of the oil was mopped up with a boom and a skimmer. Officials anticipated lifting the emergency status from the <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> over the weekend.
