<HEAD>Syrian-Christian Hostilities Escalate</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with four grafs to UPDATE with Iraqi offer to cut off
arms shipments to Christians; picks up 3rd graf, `Syrian gunners...'; DELETES
last two grafs pvs, `The Syrians...the Syrians,' to conform</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MOHAMMED SALAM</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Syrian and Lebanese Christian gunners today battled with howitzers and rocket launchers, ignoring <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> calls to halt 15 weeks of violence. Police said three people were killed and 16 wounded. The latest casualties increased the toll to 385 people killed and 1,515 wounded since the latest round in the 14-year-old civil war broke out March 8, pitting Christian army commander Gen. <PERSON> Michel </PERSON> <PERSON> Aoun </PERSON>'s units against Syrian and Druse forces. In <LOCATION> Baghdad </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> today declared it is ready to cut off arms shipments to <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>'s Christians if other countries stop providing weapons to <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>'s Moslems. `` Other countries'' was a reference to <LOCATION> Syria </LOCATION>, which has 40,000 troops in Moslem-held territory under a 1976 Arab League peacekeeping mandate. The Syrians have refused repeated calls by the <ORGANIZATION> Arab </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> League </ORGANIZATION> to lift the siege of the Christian enclave, saying they wanted guarantees that <PERSON> Aoun </PERSON> will not be able to receive war material from <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION>, their main Arab foe. Syrian gunners, deployed in Moslem west <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION> and the surrounding mountains, pounded the 310-square-mile Christian-held region northeast of the capital with 130mm howitzers and 107mm multibarrelled rocket launchers. <PERSON> Aoun </PERSON>'s gunners responded with 155mm howitzers. The spokesman said the Syrian barrage targeted two east <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION> Christian districts, the coastline north of the capital and the wooded valleys east of the waterfront, where <PERSON> Aoun </PERSON>'s artillery batteries are deployed. He said <PERSON> Aoun </PERSON>'s gunners responded against the Syrian artillery batteries along west <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION>'s seaside boulevard. A spokesman for <PERSON> Aoun </PERSON>'s command, who ref