hich precisely measure the amount'' of exposure, said <PERSON> Ruman </PERSON>. `` She should n't have been sent out without the tightest of controls, or specific written directions,'' <PERSON> Ruman </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Beyer </PERSON> does not have a listed home number and no one immediately responded to a message left Saturday on her office answering maching. Under <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION> law governing medical malpractice lawsuits, the case will be reviewed by a panel of three doctors who will rule whether there was malpractice. If the panel decides there was malpractice, the plaintiff and defendant can negotiate a settlement and the plaintiff can also seek compensation from the state Patient Compensation Fund. The maximum from the doctor and the fund is $ 500,000, insurance department officials said. If the panel rules there was n't malpractice, the plaintiff can pursue the case in the civil courts.
